Today was all about professional development, and it was an insightful experience. We heard from several guest speakers who shared valuable lessons on personal values, career success, and professional presentation.

Key Takeaways:
Defining Personal Values:

Ron Cofield led a discussion on the importance of identifying our core values. After reflecting on what matters most to me, I chose:
Faith – Staying grounded in my beliefs and principles.
Family – Prioritizing relationships and support systems.
Quality – Striving for excellence in everything I do.
Legacy – Making a lasting impact beyond my career.
Inspired by this discussion, I plan to read The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People to develop stronger personal and professional habits.
Cybersecurity Career Insights:

Paul Farley, who has worked with TrustedSec, shared his journey in the cybersecurity field. He offered practical advice on what it takes to succeed, emphasizing the importance of continuous learning, networking, and hands-on experience.
Professional Presentation for Women in Tech:

Angie Pope spoke to the women in the program about professional dress and presentation. She provided guidance on how to dress appropriately and confidently as we prepare for professional environments.

Today reinforced the idea that success isn’t just about technical skills but also values, mindset, and professional presentation. Learning from experienced professionals was inspiring, and I’m excited to apply these lessons as I move forward in my career.
